For this study, we hypothesized that:
montane Andean tree species are expected to exhibit weaker thermal acclimation of photosynthesis than lowland species, due to the widely observed thermophilization (Duque et al. 2015) and the previously documented weak thermal acclimation in African tropical montane seedlings (Dusenge et al. 2021; Wittemann et al. 2022);
